Description: Pretix Checkin List Export Plugin for NETWAYS
        =============================================
        
        This plugin adds a custom checkin list export for NETWAYS hosted events
        and conferences using .
        
        Installation
        ------------
        
        https://pypi.python.org/pypi/pretix-checkinlist-net
        
        pip
        ~~~
        
        ::
        
            pip install pretix-checkinlist-net
        
        Manual installation
        ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
        
        ::
        
            cp -rv pretix-checkinlist-net/* /usr/src/pretix-checkinlist-net/
            pip3 install /usr/src/pretix-checkinlist-net/
        
        Configuration
        -------------
        
        Navigate into the admin control panel and choose your event.
        
        ``Settings > Plugins`` and enable the plugin.
        
        ``Orders > Export > Check-in list (CSV) for NETWAYS``.
        
        Documentation
        -------------
        
        https://docs.pretix.eu/en/latest/development/api/plugins.html
        
        Checkin List Export is inspired by
        `upstream <https://github.com/pretix/pretix/blob/master/src/pretix/plugins/checkinlists/exporters.py>`__.
        
        Development setup
        -----------------
        
        1. Make sure that you have a working `pretix development
           setup <https://docs.pretix.eu/en/latest/development/setup.html>`__.
        2. Clone this repository, eg to ``local/pretix-checkinlist-net``.
        3. Activate the virtual environment you use for pretix development.
        4. Execute ``python setup.py develop`` within this directory to register
           this application with pretix’s plugin registry.
        5. Execute ``make`` within this directory to compile translations.
        6. Restart your local pretix server. You can now use the plugin from
           this repository for your events by enabling it in the ‘plugins’ tab
           in the settings.
        
        Thanks
        ======
        
        Raphael Michel for Pretix and the initial checkin list export code,
        which is adopted in this custom renderer plugin.
        
